/>\n光復香港<br />\n時代革命<br />\n<br />\n我哋係香港人!!!"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-08-15T06:28:04.000Z","msg":"唔好有任何時段得1個人當值，安全第一"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-15T06:31:06.000Z","msg":"多謝關心， 有別香港黑警， 溫哥華警察霸氣地承諾一個安全集會俾我哋<br />\n<br />\n以下係我哋嘅狀詞<br />\n<br />\nWe are a group of Hong Kong Canadians that volunteer at the previous event you helped us with.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nI am sure you know the previous event was to gain public awareness for the&nbsp;extradition bill that China is forcefully trying to pass in Hong Kong.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nThis bill basically allow China to snatch anyone they want from Hong Kong to China, including Canadian tourists.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nThis worries us as Canadians especially China had already arrested three Canadians as a political revenge since the Huawei incident in the beginning of this year.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nThe people of Hong Kong began the ongoing peaceful protests two months ago to protect everyone in the world when visiting Hong Kong.&nbsp; However, the government is allowing police brutality to augment to an unbelievably violent level that is shocks the world. Other than the peaceful protesters, many tourists also suffered from the two thousands expired tear gas that the Hong Kong police fired on the street in the last two months. Earlier this week, the Hong Kong government even allow their police to shot not only at protesters but anyone on the street with bean bags and rubber bullets in close range at head level. A bean bag shot through the safety goggle of a woman providing first aid on the street who is currently in critical condition.&nbsp; Therefore we feel the need and urgency to bring this to the attention of Canadian.&nbsp;"},{"pid":"86282bd74d106670ad21d305c0a1e667c2dcbedb","tid":1473340,"uid":8768,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-17T03:04:24.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"57a95f827611bd2092aeed919609567d1186c823","tid":1473340,"uid":169247,"like":0,"dislike"